verbose_text: Our in vivo results further confirmed that repeated subcutaneous injections of the nanoparticles loaded with a low dose of FS-344 mRNA (0.5 mg/kg) provide sustained and robust production of secreted FS-315 that is capable of decreasing serum levels of both myostatin and activin A, thereby increasing muscle mass in 17-week-old C57BL/6L mice.
